{
  "stem": "5248.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some were Lithuanian brought to Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mostly by-- when the main killing started, mostly by trucks, actually, open trucks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You could see them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They all had to sit, and they-- they were taken to the-- that would be the eastern side of the city, and-- and the same thing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, nobody.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because you see, Galicia and Lwow was-- it was considered to be an eastern province.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they did not bother-- I mean, Janowskastrasse eventually became a small concentration camp, but not others.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were no other concentration camps in eastern Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my mother paid a lot of money to have me taken out, and the event was that people-- that was actually started with the Ukrainian policemen and some other people.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would-- they would take me out of Lwow, and then bring back to Lwow when-- when the-- when the shooting started, just to-- because in a small town, it was much harder to survive.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You were much more conspicuous.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the agreement was that my-- that my mother and my brother would follow me but, of course, they never-- it got too late, all the people who did it for me got frightened to do it.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A little bit before, a little bit before the shooting.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, OK, wait-- there was a camp in between Janowskastrasse.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Actually, I left ghetto a couple of times.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First, I-- I got-- when ghetto was still there and the camp was not yet in reality, I always felt that the only way to survive is to leave the ghetto, and I tried the very first time.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the people who were supposed to give me a shelter, they got frightened.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I had to go back to ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
